<TITLE> Govt ready to face SIDR ravages: chief adviser </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 15 (bdnews24.com)  Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed Thursday announced that the government was all set to face the approaching cyclone SIDR. "A most terrible cyclone is rushing towards the Bangladesh coasts. The government is all set to face the disaster," he said at the launch of the BATEXPO 2007 show organised by BGMEA. The interim administration head asked the nation to pray so that the people living in the coastal areas could cope with the ravages of the devastating tropical storm. bdnews24
